# Rules to create reports/news posts Markdown files

- Filenames must not contain `/`. Spacing should be represented with `-` or `_`, choose one and be consistent. E.g. "july-report.md"
- Keep the filenames short and simple, 4-5 words max.
- Files must end with `.md`.

- Files must include metadata at the start. Required metadata:
  - `title`: Short title for the report/news post. Used by index page.
  - `description`: Short description of the report/news post. Used by index page.
  - The metadata must be formatted as follows:

```yaml
---
title: report title name
description: report short description
---
```
